        "Ongoing Events": "Marathon - Robinson: the 12,000 bpd coker was shut during the morning of July 6. The 43,000 bpd catalytic reformer was restarted during the morning of July 4. Increased activity began at the unit during the afternoon of July 2 (EST). The unit was shut on June 24. The 24,000 bpd reformer feed hydrotreater was shut dur- ing the late evening of July 1 (EST). Marathon - Detroit: multiple units were shut during the evening of July 5. Units include the 147,000 bpd CDU, 55,000 bpd VDU, 35,000 bpd FCC, 21,500 bpd catalytic reformer, 28,000 bpd coker and 7,000 bpd kerosene hydrotreater. The 34,000 bpd reformer feed hydrotreater was shut on November 17, 2025 and remained offline. Marathon - Mandan: the 12,500 bpd catalytic reformer, 23,800 bpd diesel hydrotreater, 4,300 bpd gasoline hydrotreater, 4,400 bpd alkylation unit and sulfur recovery unit were restarted during the morning of July 2. Increased activity began at the diesel hydrotreater, gasoline hydrotreater and alkylation unit during the morning of July 1. The 74,000 bpd CDU and 27,000 bpd FCC were restarted during the morning of July 1. All monitored units were shut during the evening of June 29. HF Sinclair - Tulsa (West): the 8,500 bpd coker was shut during the morning of July 1.",
